# Project 005 — Writing Release Notes

## Date

2026-07-24

## Category

Technical Writing

## Difficulty

Intermediate

## Focus

Release Documentation, Product Communication, Change Logs

---

# Objective

Write professional release notes for a new software version. The release notes should clearly communicate new features, improvements, bug fixes, breaking changes, and known issues.

---

# Scenario

A project management application is releasing **Version 2.5.0** with several new features and improvements.

### Changes Included

- Added Dark Mode
- Added Two-Factor Authentication (2FA)
- Improved dashboard loading speed
- Fixed file upload failures
- Fixed notification duplication bug
- Improved mobile responsiveness
- Deprecated legacy calendar integration
- Some users may experience delayed email notifications

---

# Evaluation Criteria

| Criteria | Description |
|----------|-------------|
| Clarity | Are the updates easy to understand? |
| Organization | Are the changes grouped logically? |
| Completeness | Are all important updates included? |
| Professionalism | Does the document follow industry standards? |
| Readability | Can users quickly identify relevant changes? |

---

# Release Notes

# Version 2.5.0

**Release Date:** July 24, 2026

We're excited to introduce Version 2.5.0, bringing new security features, performance improvements, and important bug fixes to enhance your experience.

---

## ✨ New Features

### Dark Mode

Users can now switch between Light Mode and Dark Mode for a more comfortable viewing experience.

### Two-Factor Authentication (2FA)

Added optional two-factor authentication to provide an additional layer of account security during sign-in.

---

## 🚀 Improvements

- Improved dashboard loading performance.
- Enhanced mobile responsiveness across supported devices.
- Optimized application stability and responsiveness.

---

## 🐞 Bug Fixes

- Fixed an issue that caused file uploads to fail under certain conditions.
- Resolved duplicate notification messages appearing for some users.

---

## ⚠️ Deprecations

### Legacy Calendar Integration

Support for the legacy calendar integration has been deprecated and will be removed in a future release.

Users should begin migrating to the new calendar integration.

---

## Known Issues

Some users may experience delayed email notifications.

Our engineering team is actively investigating this issue, and a fix will be included in a future update.

---

## Upgrade Recommendation

All users are encouraged to upgrade to Version 2.5.0 to benefit from improved security, better performance, and important bug fixes.

---

# Why These Release Notes Are Effective

- Clearly separates features, improvements, bug fixes, and known issues.
- Uses concise, user-friendly language.
- Highlights important changes without unnecessary technical detail.
- Follows a consistent structure commonly used in software releases.
- Helps users understand what has changed and whether any action is required.

---

# Reflection

## What I Learned

Good release notes balance completeness with brevity. Users want to quickly understand what's new, what's fixed, and whether they need to take any action after updating.

---

## What I'd Do Differently

For enterprise software, I would also include:

- Supported platform versions
- Security advisories
- Migration instructions
- Links to detailed documentation
- Issue tracking references

